First and foremost, as with any language, you should NOT choose C++ as a way to show off if you don‚Äôt know it well. Make sure that you pick a language you are very comfortable with, have practiced interview questions with, and ideally have worked in recently (though not strictly required).
Outside of that, here are some things you should try to avoid when interviewing in C++ specifically.
Mismanaging Memory
C++ gives you manual control over memory. This can lead to problems if you don't manage memory correctly. For example, the following code results in a memory leak because memory allocated with new
